article.description: — Xavier Bishop had 22 points as Montana State beat Idaho State 71-63 in the quarterfinals of the Big Sky Conference Tournament on Thursday.
article.headline: Bishop scores 22 to lift Montana St. past Idaho St. 71-63
article.linkText: Bishop scores 22 to lift Montana St. past Idaho St. 71-63
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- — Xavier Bishop had 22 points as Montana State beat Idaho State 71-63 in the quarterfinals of the Big Sky Conference Tournament on Thursday. Bishop hit all 11 of his free throws. Jubrile Belo had 19 points for fifth seed Montana State (12-9). Amin Adamu added 10 points and seven rebounds. Abdul Mohamed had nine rebounds. Tarik Cool had 18 points for the fourth seed Bengals (13-11). Austin Smellie added 11 points and seven rebounds. Brayden Parker had 10 points. Montana State will play top seed Southern Utah in a Friday semifinal the first time in 12 years the Bobcats have been in the semis. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
